        <tr><td>Steam generator sensor</td><td>$480 to $780</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Convection fan motor</td><td>$700 to $980</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door gasket</td><td>$320 to $480</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Touchscreen / control panel (Rational SCC)</td><td>$1,200 to $1,800</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Water inlet valve</td><td>$260 to $420</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Drain pump</td><td>$420 to $620</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Heating element</td><td>$680 to $980</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Multi-component repair</td><td>$1,400 to $3,000</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Warranty</td><td>90 days parts plus labor</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 06 BRANDS WE SERVICE -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">06 · Brands</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Combi oven brands we service.</h2>

    <ul class="brand-list">
      <li><strong>Rational</strong> (independent, German). Dominant in LA premium kitchens. SelfCookingCenter (SCC) legacy line and iCombi Pro current generation. Different parts catalogs. <a href="/brands/rational-combi-oven-repair/">Rational combi oven repair brand page</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Alto-Shaam</strong> (independent, Wisconsin family company since 1955, Halco family). Combitherm CT Express and CT Proformance lines. Common in hotel banquet kitchens. <a href="/brands/alto-shaam-oven-repair/">Alto-Shaam oven repair brand page</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Convotherm</strong> (Welbilt subsidiary). OEB series. Common in mid-tier banquet operations.</li>
      <li><strong>Henny Penny</strong> (independent, Ohio family company). FlexFusion combi line. Less common in LA than Rational or Alto-Shaam but fully supported.</li>
      <li><strong>Unox</strong> (independent, Italian). ChefTop XEVC and XEBC series. Growing presence in LA mid-tier restaurants.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 07 WHY US -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">07 · Why operators call us</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Six reasons.</h2>

    <ul class="why-list">
      <li><strong>SoCal hard water descaling expertise.</strong> Annual descaling is the single highest-ROI maintenance investment for any combi oven in LA, OC, or the Inland Empire. We do this routinely.</li>
      <li><strong>Rational SCC vs iCombi Pro generation awareness.</strong> Different parts catalogs. We identify by serial number first.</li>
      <li><strong>Alto-Shaam, Convotherm, Henny Penny coverage.</strong> Not just Rational. Multi-brand combi service across all five SoCal counties.</li>
      <li><strong>BHGS Licensed #A49573 plus EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410).</strong> See our <a href="/credentials/licensed/">licensing page</a> and <a href="/credentials/epa-certified/">EPA 608 page</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>$120 commercial diagnostic, no after-hours surcharge.</strong> Phones answered 24/7.</li>
      <li><strong>Annual descaling contracts available.</strong> Predictable maintenance budget. Fleet pricing for 3+ machines.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Sister sub-services: <a href="/commercial/oven-repair/convection-oven-repair/">convection oven repair</a>, <a href="/commercial/oven-repair/rotisserie-oven-repair/">rotisserie oven repair</a>. Parent: <a href="/commercial/oven-repair/">commercial oven repair pillar</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 08 FAQ -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">08 · FAQ</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Combi oven repair, common questions.</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      {faqs.map(f => (
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>{f.q}</summary>
          <p set:html={f.a} />
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 09 BOTTOM CTA -->
<section class="bottom-cta">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Combi oven down? Call us 24/7.</h2>
    <p>Rational, Alto-Shaam, Convotherm specialists. SoCal hard water descaling. BHGS Licensed #A49573. $120 commercial diagnostic.</p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a href={phoneHref} class="btn-primary">☎ Call {phone}</a>
      <a href="/contact/" class="btn-secondary">Book Online</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</Layout>

<style>
  :root { --red: #C8102E; --black: #0a0a0a; --gray: #f5f5f5; --border: #e2e2e2; --text: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b; }
